<tip category="KOrganizer|General">
<html>
<p>...that you can synchronize your calendar data with the data on a Palm Pilot
by using <a href="http://www.slac.com/pilone/kpilot_home">KPilot</a>?
</html>
</tip>

<tip category="KOrganizer|General">
<html>
<p>...that you can select whether the week starts on Monday or on Sunday in the KDE
control center? KOrganizer uses this setting. Look at Personalization -> Country &
Languages, on the Time & Dates tab.
</html>
</tip>

<tip category="KOrganizer|General">
<html>
<p>...that you can store your calendar on an FTP server? Use the standard file
dialog to save the calendar to a URL like "ftp://username@ftpserver/filename".
You can make your calendar active and load and save it as if it were local.
Just make sure that no two KOrganizer applications are working on the same file, at
the same time.
</html>
</tip>

<tip category="KOrganizer|General">
<html>
<p>...that you can create hierarchical To-Dos by clicking with the right mouse
button on an existing To-Do and selecting "New Sub-To-Do" from the context menu?
</html>
</tip>
